{
    "id": "elem.4.7",
    "n": 7,
    "type": "proposition",
    "enunciation": "`About a given circle to circumscribe a square`.",
    "proof": [
        {
            "text": "Let `ABCD` be the given circle; thus it is required to circumscribe a square about the circle `ABCD`.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "ABCD",
                "ABCD"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Let two diameters `AC`, `BD` of the circle `ABCD` be drawn at right angles to one another, and through the points `A`, `B`, `C`, `D` let `FG`, `GH`, `HK`, `KF` be drawn touching the circle `ABCD`. [elem.3.16.p.1]",
            "refs": [
                "elem.3.16.p.1"
            ],
            "emphs": [
                "AC",
                "BD",
                "ABCD",
                "A",
                "B",
                "C",
                "D",
                "FG",
                "GH",
                "HK",
                "KF",
                "ABCD"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Then, since `FG` touches the circle `ABCD`, and `EA` has been joined from the centre `E` to the point of contact at `A`,",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "FG",
                "ABCD",
                "EA",
                "E",
                "A"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For the same reason",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, since the angle `AEB` is right, and the angle `EBG` is also right,",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "AEB",
                "EBG"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For the same reason",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Similarly we can prove that",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore `GK`, `GC`, `AK`, `FB`, `BK` are parallelograms; therefore `GF` is equal to `HK`, and `GH` to `FK`. [elem.1.34]",
            "refs": [
                "elem.1.34"
            ],
            "emphs": [
                "GK",
                "GC",
                "AK",
                "FB",
                "BK",
                "GF",
                "HK",
                "GH",
                "FK"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "And, since `AC` is equal to `BD`, and `AC` is also equal to each of the straight lines `GH`, `FK`,",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "AC",
                "BD",
                "AC",
                "GH",
                "FK"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "I say next that it is also right-angled.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": []
        },
        {
            "text": "For, since `GBEA` is a parallelogram, and the angle `AEB` is right, therefore the angle `AGB` is also right. [elem.1.34]",
            "refs": [
                "elem.1.34"
            ],
            "emphs": [
                "GBEA",
                "AEB",
                "AGB"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Similarly we can prove that",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore `FGHK` is right-angled.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "FGHK"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "But it was also proved equilateral;  and it has been circumscribed about the circle `ABCD`.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "ABCD"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore about the given circle a square has been circumscribed. Q. E. F.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": []
        }
    ]
}